EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to health care; requiring a medical facility or a provider of health
care who receives notice from a patient of [or otherwise discovers a
potential] an error in a medical bill to review the potential error and
refund any overpayment; authorizing certain disciplinary action for
the failure to comply with such requirements; requiring the
Governor’s Consumer Health Advocate to provide certain
assistance concerning medical billing errors; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides every patient of a medical facility with the right to examine the bill
2 for his or her care and receive an explanation of the bill. (NRS 449A.106) Existing law also
3 requires each provider of health care to timely provide a patient with an itemized bill at no
4 additional cost to the patient. (NRS 629.071) Sections 2 and 3 of this bill, respectively,
5 require a medical facility or provider of health care that [determines or] receives notice from
6 a patient that a medical bill [may contain] contains one or more specific billing errors to: (1)
7 [review the potential] respond to the patient concerning the billing errors [;] , including by
