12 respectively, authorize the suspension or revocation of the license of a medical facility that
13 violates section 2, and the imposition of disciplinary action against and administrator of
14 certain facilities who aids or abets a violation of section 2.] that the disputed charge is being
15 reviewed. Sections 2 and 3 require the medical facility or provider of health care to
16 refund any overpayment by the patient. Section 2 requires the State Board of Health to
17 establish by regulation an administrative fine to impose on a medical facility that
18 violates section 2. Section 3 authorizes the imposition of disciplinary action against a
19 provider of health care who fails to comply with the requirements of section 3. Section 2.5 of
20 this bill requires the Governor’s Consumer Health Advocate, who serves as the head of
21 the Office, to review medical bills that consumers believe to be erroneous and assist
22 consumers in addressing medical billing errors.

